{{Short description|American painter}} {{multiple issues| {{BLP primary sources|date=July 2013}} {{BLP sources|date=July 2013}} {{more footnotes|date=January 2014}} }}
{{Infobox artist | bgcolour = | name = Dennis Wojtkiewicz | image = | imagesize = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = 1956 | birth_place = [[Chicago]], [[Illinois]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=1499&dat=19830508&id=hWcaAAAAIBAJ&sjid=9CkEAAAAIBAJ&pg=5210,6138422|title=Photography Dominates at West Bend|last=Auer|first=James|date=8 May 1983|work=[[The Milwaukee Journal]]|accessdate=21 January 2014}}</ref> | death_date = | death_place = | nationality = [[Poland|Polish]] | field = [[Painting]] | training = | movement = [[Hyperrealism]] | works = Art | patrons = | influenced = | awards = }} '''Dennis Wojtkiewicz''' (born 1956, Chicago, Illinois) is an American [[Hyperrealism (painting)|Hyperrealist]] painter and draughtsman.
Wojtkiewicz graduated from [[Southern Illinois University]] and is artist associated with the Hyperrealist movement. He is best known for his large scale renderings of sliced fruit and flowers. In order to achieve his desired effect, technically, Wojtkiewicz relies on traditional oil paint and brushes with a classical application, he also uses pastel for his drawings.
Dennis Wojtkiewicz has exhibited his work in leading fine art galleries in the United States and abroad. His work is owned by many leading private, corporate and public collections including the Evanston Museum of Art, [[Fidelity Investments]] in Boston and the [[University of South Dakota]].
==Selected solo exhibitions== * 2000 M.A. Doran Gallery, Tulsa, OK * 2012 Art Revolution Taipei International Art Fair, Taipei World Trade Center, Taipei, Taiwan * 2014 Sugarman Peterson Gallery, Santa Fe, NM * 2012 Peterson-Cody Gallery, Santa Fe, NM * 2009 Peterson-Cody Gallery, Santa fe, NM * 2006 J. Cacciola Gallery, New York, NY
