{{refimprove|date=July 2018}} {{Infobox scientist |name = Peter Jacob Hjelm |image = |image_size = |caption = Peter Jacob Hjelm |birth_date = {{birth date|1746|10|2|df=y}} |birth_place = [[Sunnerbo härad]], [[Småland]], [[Sweden]] |residence = |nationality = |death_date = {{death date and age|1813|10|7|1746|10|2|df=y}} |death_place = [[Stockholm]], [[Sweden]] |field = |work_institution = |alma_mater = [[University of Uppsala]] |doctoral_advisor = |doctoral_students = |known_for = |prizes = |religion = |footnotes = }}'''Peter (Petter) Jacob Hjelm''' (2 October 1746 – 7 October 1813) was a Swedish chemist and the first person to isolate the element [[molybdenum]] in 1781, four years after its discovery.<ref>{{cite journal | author = P. J. Hjelm | title = Versuche mit Molybdäna, und Reduction der selben Erde | journal = svenska vetensk. Academ. Handlingar | pages = 268 | year = 1788 | volume = 49 | issue = | url = https://books.google.de/books?id=uBVnAAAAcAAJ&pg=PA268 }} </ref> == Life == After his studies at the [[University of Uppsala]] he received his Ph.D. He became professor at the Mining academy and in 1782 he became head of the [[Royal Mint]]. From 1784 on he was a member of the [[Royal Swedish Academy of Sciences]]. His last position was at the laboratory of the Ministry of Mining.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Association |first1=IMOA International Molybdenum |title=Molybdenum history |url=https://www.imoa.info/molybdenum/molybdenum-history.php |website=www.imoa.info |accessdate=11 July 2018}}</ref>
