{{Infobox book | name = The Greatest Story Ever Told—So Far: Why Are We Here? | author = [[Lawrence M. Krauss]] | illustrator = | image = The Greatest Story Ever Told - So Far.jpg | caption = Hardcover edition | published = March 21, 2017 | subject = Physics | genre = Non-fiction | publisher = [[Atria Books]] | country = United States | language = English | media_type = Print, e-book | isbn = 978-1-4767-7761-0 | dewey = | congress = | oclc = | pages = 336 pp. | website = | preceded_by = [[A Universe from Nothing]] | followed_by = }}
'''''The Greatest Story Ever Told—So Far: Why Are We Here?''''' is the tenth full-length non-fiction book by the American theoretical physicist [[Lawrence M. Krauss]]. The book was initially published on March 21, 2017 by [[Atria Books]].<ref>{{cite web|title=The Greatest Story Ever Told— So Far: Why Are We Here? Lawrence M. Krauss. Atria, $27 (336p) ISBN 978-1-4767-7761-0|url=https://www.publishersweekly.com/978-1-4767-7761-0|website=[[Publishers Weekly]]|accessdate=31 July 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Moskowitz|first1=Clara|title=Q&A: Lawrence Krauss on The Greatest Story Ever Told|url=https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/q-a-lawrence-krauss-on-the-greatest-story-ever-told/|website=[[Scientific American]]|accessdate=31 July 2017|date=March 21, 2017}}</ref>
==Synopsis== The book deals with the current scientific understanding of the creation of the Universe and gives a history of how scientists have formulated the [[Standard Model of Particle Physics]].
